SIMPLE: tollbooth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tollbooth
<hw>Toll"booth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Toll</ets> a
tax + <ets>booth</ets>.]</ety> <ety>[Written also
<ets>tolbooth</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place where goods are
weighed to ascertain the duties or toll.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He saw Levy . . . sitting at the <qex>tollbooth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wyclif (Mark ii. 14).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In Scotland, a burgh jail; hence, any prison,
especially a town jail.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tollbooth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tollbooth
<hw>Toll"booth`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To imprison in a
tollbooth.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That they might <qex>tollbooth</qex> Oxford men.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Corbet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toller</ent>⟦br⟧
